Prognostycacion, and almanacke of two shepherdes necessarye for all housholders,
[16] p.
Imprynte[d] by me Robert wyer: dwe[l]lynge in Seynt Martyns parysshe, in the Duke of Suffolkes rentges [sic], besyde charynge Crosse, [[London] : [1556]]
Partly in verse. With a title-page woodcut. Printer's name and address from colophon. Signatures: A-B⁴. Last page contains "Almanacke, for a. M.D.lvi.". Identified as STC 20425 on UMI microfilm. Reproduction of a photostat of the original in the Henry E. Huntington Library and Art Gallery.
